literals:
"a room made of mossy old stone, clearly once someone's home.
The floor is riddled with bones, waste, and rotten food.
The air is humid and putrid, moving heavily through your nostrils.

From the shadows out of sight, you hear a guteral scream as a monster lunges forward at you!"
"\nYou ask the inn keeper for directions as you happily oblige, before setting off down the road to where the monsters are reported to be.\n"

"Your weary feet lead you into a small farm town nestled in the woods.
Seeking a warm place to rest, you head into an inn.
The inn keeper eyes your sword and excitedly greets you.
"

"Inn Keeper: Hello adventurer!
Welcome to the town of Sorrowsoot. We are glad you came, we have been struggling with some monsters nearby!
You can stay the night for free if you rid us of them!
"
"Ever low on cash, you agree to help the town in exchange for a good night's sleep...\n"
"You return, bloody and bruised back to the inn.\n\"The job is done. Give me a room, a beer, and a sandwich.\", you say to the inn keeper"
"\"Gladly!\" the inn keeper says and you proceed to have a well earned night's dinner and a rest."

"A C# group project by Roderick Walker and Jordan Hershberger






"
